A great example of how this subnet works can be seen by looking at the SN96 validator from our good friends at Rizzo (one of the other few remaining true ecosystem-wide validators). 

*Not picking on them or throwing shade in any way, but since their validator also had to "start again" with the evaluations 1 epoch ago due to various circumstances, they make a perfect 'visual' example to demonstrate how things work on this subnet.*

As you can see, it has set weights for only 3 random miners. Rizzo didn't pick which 3. Rizzo didn't manually set for these 3. There is only 3 weights set because the validator only evaluates 3 miners every epoch... and next epoch, I expect to see 6 lines on that graph.

But here's the kicker: 4 days is a bloody long time, especially in Bittensor. A lot can change in that time. Some new miners come, sole old miners go, your miner might be down for the 10 minutes in the 72 minutes in the 4 days that a given validator randomly selects you for your turn... and that means that the weights between all of the validators may vary significantly.

Because, again... it's 3 random miners, and not the same 3 random miners across all of the validators either... It's 3 different random miners across each of the validators.
